<reference id="api_onuserinfoupdated">
    <title><ph keyref="onUserInfoUpdated"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Occurs when the SDK gets the user ID and user account of the remote user.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
   <keywords>
       <indexterm keyref="onUserInfoUpdated" />
   </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody><section id="prototype">
        
        <p outputclass="codeblock" conref="../conref/conref_rtc_api.dita#apidef/onUserInfoUpdated"/>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc">
   
   <dl outputclass="since">
       <dlentry>
  <dt>Since</dt>
  <dd>v2.8.0</dd>
       </dlentry>
   </dl>
   <p>After a remote user joins the channel, the SDK gets the UID and user account of the remote user, caches them in a mapping table object (userInfo), and triggers this callback on the local client.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters"><title>Parameters</title>
   <parml>
       <plentry>
  <pt>uid</pt>
  <pd>The ID of the remote user.</pd>
       </plentry>
       <plentry>
  <pt>userInfo</pt>
  <pd>The object that contains the user ID and user account of the remote user. See <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> for details.</pd>
       </plentry>
   </parml>
        </section>
</refbody>
</reference>
